originalText.text:
At first, there was wonderful service from this agency.  Each month the premium would be taken off my checking account...all was well.  Then I purchased another policy.  The agent who opened the policy was polite and nice, and everything went fine.  I even wrote a nice review for him.  Then the day came when I had to report a loss.  My first taste of something going wrong was when I called the office to add to my claim.  I was told by another agent that she would add the information because my agent was not in the office.  The next day when I spoke to my agent, I was told that the additional loss items could not be added because it was too late.
What a circus between my agent and the underwriting department.  I had to call several times to get anything done. I called the agent and told him what was happening.  I received an email that informed me that the claim had been denied. I called the agent and was told that he never received that notice.  I got so fed up with having to call nearly every day that I tried to reach the owner.  First I asked for her number, but no one had it.  I went online and got the information.   I sent her a message.  To this day, I have not received a response from her.
I made one of my usual calls to the claims department.  I was lucky enough to reach a nice and knowledgeable claims officer, who listened to my woes. She went through the claim with me.  It was found that the policy had a host of items claimed as losses.  The only item that was claimed as a loss was a computer monitor.  She went through everything on the claim report.  Then issued a payout.
The next day, I received an email from another agent telling me that the underwriting department needed more information about the losses and that if not received the claim would be denied.  I replied in an email telling the agent that the claim had been settled.  I also called my agent and left a message telling him the same thing. I have not heard from either of them.

Today, called my agent to request that the policies be terminated. I was told he would have to call me back.  I sent him an email just in case he is unable to get back to me.
